Find the sum of odd numbers from 1 to n, i.e. 1 + 3 + 5 + ...

Write a function called sumOfOdd that takes n as an argument and returns the sum of odd numbers from 1 to n. Use a while loop when solving.

Examples:

sumOfOdd (1) must return 1;
sumOfOdd (3) must return 4;
sumOfOdd (20) must return 100.

Solution:
function sumOfOdd(n){
let sum;
n % 2 !== 0 ? sum = n : sum = 0;
 while (n >= 1) {
    n = n - 1;
   if (n % 2 !== 0) {
      sum += n;
   }
 }
 return sum;
}
